# Agrova — Design System

## Overview

Agrova is used by two very different people on two very different surfaces:

1. A low-literacy field worker, one-handed, outdoors, possibly wearing gloves, on a $100 Android phone.
2. An owner, at a desk, scanning 500 fields and dozens of open tasks across a wide screen.

The design system unifies them behind a shared token set but enforces **adaptive density**: worker screens get double the whitespace and 1.5× the type size of owner screens. Every UI decision is tested against both personas.

`DESIGN.md` at the repo root is the single source of truth for visual tokens and component specs. This rule tells you when and how to consult it.

## When to Use

- Building any new screen, component, or UI primitive
- Modifying any existing UI
- Reviewing a PR that touches visual code
- Deciding whether a design decision needs a spec update
- Debugging a visual regression

**When NOT to use:** Pure backend, data-model, or tooling changes with no UI surface.

## The Design Loop

```
  READ DESIGN.md   ──→   IMPLEMENT  ──→   VERIFY
       │                     │              │
       ▼                     ▼              ▼
  Know the token        Use the token   Check both surfaces,
  before you reach      directly, not   contrast, touch
  for a hex code        a one-off       targets, Turkish
                        value           diacritics
```

### Step 1: Read DESIGN.md First

Before writing a single line of JSX, open `DESIGN.md` and locate the relevant section:

- Section 2 — Color tokens
- Section 3 — Typography scale
- Section 4 — Component specs (buttons, cards, chips, inputs, activity icons)
- Section 5 — Layout + adaptive density rules
- Section 8 — Accessibility floor
- Section 11 — Quick reference snippets

If what you need isn't in `DESIGN.md`, that's a signal — either you're building something truly new (propose a spec addition) or you're about to duplicate a pattern that already exists under a different name (search first).

### Step 2: Implement With Tokens

Never hardcode a color, spacing, radius, font size, or weight. Use the token.

```tsx
// ✅ Good — tokens from DESIGN.md § 2 and § 4
<button className="
  w-full h-[72px] rounded-full px-6
  bg-orchard-500 hover:bg-orchard-700 active:scale-[0.97]
  text-white text-xl font-semibold
  transition-all duration-150
  focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-orchard-500 focus-visible:ring-offset-2
">
  {t`Bitir`}
</button>

// ❌ Bad — arbitrary values, wrong weight, no focus ring, raw label
<button className="
  w-full h-[60px] rounded-lg px-4
  bg-[#4CAF50] hover:bg-[#388E3C]
  text-white text-lg font-bold
">
  Bitir
</button>
```

### Step 3: Verify On Both Surfaces

Every component you build or change must be checked against:

- **Worker surface:** 375×667 viewport (iPhone SE baseline), touch targets ≥ 72px primary and ≥ 56px otherwise, base font ≥ 18px, no text inputs.
- **Owner surface:** 1440×900 viewport, sidebar navigation, dense tables allowed, Cmd+K accessible.

Run the built-in theme and locale checks:

- Light mode + dark mode (system toggle)
- Turkish diacritics rendering (`İçeri`, `Öğlen`, `Şeftali`, `Çapa`, `Güneş`, `Ülkü`)
- `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` collapses animations

## The Non-Negotiables

These come from `DESIGN.md §8` and `§10`. Every PR that violates them is a blocker.

### Accessibility floor

- WCAG AA minimum (4.5:1 text, 3:1 UI) everywhere
- WCAG AAA (7:1) on worker primary action buttons
- Worker primary actions: **≥ 72px tall**, full-width
- All interactive elements: **≥ 56px** on mobile, **≥ 40px** on desktop
- Worker screens: base font **≥ 18px**
- Every interactive element has a visible focus ring (`ring-2 ring-orchard-500 ring-offset-2`)
- No free-text keyboard input on worker screens — use pickers, numpads, photo, voice
- Every icon has an `aria-label` in Turkish
- All action-confirmation flows use a second-screen confirm (prevents mis-taps with gloves)
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` and `prefers-color-scheme`

### Typography discipline

- Inter Variable with `"cv11","ss01","calt"` set globally
- Only three weights: **400, 500, 600**. Never 700+, never 300.
- Never `#FFF` or `#000` on text — use `text-primary` / `text-secondary` tokens
- Tabular numerals on any number that could be compared (counts, IDs, prices)

### Color discipline

- `orchard-500` is the only chromatic accent in UI chrome
- `harvest-500` is for highlights only — never on a primary CTA
- Status colors appear only in status chips and progress indicators, never as general accents
- No drop shadows — depth via surface steps + hairline borders
- Dark mode uses the tokens from `DESIGN.md §2`, not inverted light mode

### Motion discipline

- 150ms for state transitions
- 250ms for page fades
- Primary CTAs: `scale(1.02)` hover, `scale(0.97)` active. Nothing more dramatic.
- Worker mobile: **no** route-change animations (motion sickness risk for outdoor users)
- Collapse all motion to 0ms when `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`

## Adaptive Density — The Core Rule

Worker and owner screens share tokens but apply different step values.

```
                 OWNER WEB        WORKER MOBILE
Card padding     16px             24px  (×1.5)
Stack gap        12px             20px  (×1.67)
Base font        16px             18px  (×1.13)
Primary CTA      36px tall        72px tall (×2)
Icon chrome      20px             28px  (×1.4)
Max text width   ~720px           viewport width
```

Never copy an owner component into a worker screen without re-tuning the spacing. The easiest test: if the worker screen feels "crowded", it is — you skipped the step-up.

## Component Library Protocol

Agrova uses **shadcn/ui** as the primitive layer. When you need a new component:

1. Check if `shadcn` already has it (`Button`, `Dialog`, `Select`, etc.)
2. Install it via the shadcn CLI into `src/components/ui/`
3. Immediately re-skin it to match `DESIGN.md` tokens — do not ship the default shadcn look
4. Add a worker-density variant if the component will be used on mobile
5. Document which sections of `DESIGN.md` it implements in a top-of-file comment

```tsx
// src/components/ui/button.tsx
// Implements: DESIGN.md §4 Buttons (Primary CTA — both surfaces)
// Worker variant: size="lg" (72px tall, pill)
// Owner variant:  size="md" (36px tall, rounded-8)

export const buttonVariants = cva(
  'inline-flex items-center justify-center font-semibold transition-all ...',
  {
    variants: {
      size: {
        md: 'h-9 rounded-lg px-4 text-sm',
        lg: 'h-[72px] rounded-full px-6 text-xl',
      },
      variant: { primary: '...', secondary: '...', ghost: '...' },
    },
  },
)
```

## When DESIGN.md Is Incomplete

If you hit a design decision that `DESIGN.md` doesn't cover:

1. **Stop.** Don't invent a token on the fly.
2. Propose an addition: write the token / rule in a PR against `DESIGN.md` first.
3. Get it reviewed separately from the feature PR, even if it's a one-line addition.
4. Then use the new token in the feature PR.

This prevents token sprawl and keeps the system coherent.

## Visual Regression Protocol

For any UI change:

- Capture before/after screenshots at both worker (375px) and owner (1440px) widths
- Capture light and dark mode
- Check Turkish diacritics in every headline size (40/32/24/18px)
- Post the screenshots in the PR description

## Icon Protocol

- UI chrome: Lucide React, stroke 1.75px
- Activity icons: custom SVG components in `src/components/icons/activities/`, same line-weight as Lucide
- Sizes: 16 / 20 / 24 / 28 / 32 for Lucide; 24 inline + 96 for worker task cards
- Never mix icon sets inside a single component — if Lucide doesn't have it, either design a custom icon in the same style or pick a close-enough Lucide icon

## Do

- Read `DESIGN.md` **before** writing UI
- Use tokens for every color, spacing, radius, font size, and weight
- Apply adaptive density — worker screens breathe, owner screens pack
- Ship with keyboard focus rings on every interactive element
- Test Turkish diacritics at every type size before merging
- Use semantic HTML first (`<button>`, `<a>`, `<label>`) before reaching for `<div role=...>`
- Confirm destructive actions on a second screen on worker surfaces
- Include screenshots in PR descriptions for UI changes

## Don't

- Don't hardcode colors, spacings, or radii
- Don't use weight 700 or higher
- Don't use drop shadows on cards
- Don't put text inputs on worker screens without explicit spec approval
- Don't animate route changes on worker mobile
- Don't copy an owner component into mobile without re-tuning density
- Don't ship raw shadcn default styling — always re-skin
- Don't introduce a new color or size that isn't in `DESIGN.md`

## Common Rationalizations

| Rationalization | Reality |
|---|---|
| "I just need a slightly different green here" | That's how systems die. Use `orchard-500` or propose an extension to `DESIGN.md`. |
| "One-off shadow won't hurt" | It will. The no-shadow rule is how the system feels coherent. Use surface steps. |
| "56px is tall enough, we don't really need 72" | Workers wear gloves. 72px is the floor for primary actions. Non-negotiable. |
| "Turkish fits fine, no need to test all diacritics" | Test `İ`, `ı`, `ğ`, `ş` at every type size. `İ` at 40px is where Inter most often fails without `ss01`. |
| "The dark mode will look fine if I just invert" | It won't. Dark mode has its own surface and text tokens. Use them. |

## Red Flags

- Any hex color or arbitrary Tailwind value in JSX (`bg-[#...]`, `text-[#...]`, `p-[13px]`)
- `font-bold` or weight ≥ 700 anywhere
- `shadow-*` utilities in UI chrome (allowed only on modal backdrops)
- A worker screen with a `<input type="text">` or `<textarea>`
- An interactive element without `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-orchard-500`
- A component with one codepath and two call sites (owner and worker) with no density variant
- An `aria-label` in English
- A headline with ASCII-only text where it should have Turkish diacritics (`Cifltik` instead of `Çiftlik`)

## Verification

Before opening a PR for any UI change:

- [ ] Tokens from `DESIGN.md` used for every color, spacing, radius, font size, weight
- [ ] Accessibility floor met (contrast, touch targets, focus rings, keyboard paths)
- [ ] Worker surface and owner surface both visually verified
- [ ] Light and dark mode both verified
- [ ] Turkish diacritics render correctly at every size shown
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` path verified
- [ ] `aria-label` and `alt` attributes are Turkish
- [ ] Screenshots attached to PR
- [ ] No new tokens invented without a companion `DESIGN.md` update
